Provinces are preparing to play their part in rolling out vaccines. On Tuesday we heard the comprehensive plans from the KwaZulu Natal premier. On Wednesday in the Eastern Cape legislature the health MEC Sindiswa Gomba confirmed the province would receive its part of the AstraZeneca vaccine on 9 February. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Provinces are finalising plans for the COVID-19 vaccine rollout. KwaZulu Natal has already outlined its plans for when it receives the jabs on 14 February. WATCH: COVID-19: 200 vaccine sites identified The Eastern Cape is planning to begin the rollout next Tuesday. A challenge for the province will be keeping the vaccines cold. On Wednesday, Health Minister, Zweli Mkhize, said the COVID-19 vaccine rollout will be managed using the Electronic Vaccination Data System (EVDS).